Git:

---A version control system (VCS).

---Helps track changes in code, manage versions, and collaborate with others.

---Works locally on your computer.

GitHub:

A cloud-based platform that hosts Git repositories.

Provides collaboration features like pull requests, issues, project boards.

Makes it easier to share code and work with teams.

